## **Notes**

### Using CSS

- Link to the CSS file in the head of the HTML

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css" />
```

### CSS Syntax

- Styles content we wrote in HTML using "rules"
- Rules broken into Selectors and Decleration block
  - Decleration block broken into declerations
  - Declerations broken into properties and values

```css
p {
  color: red;
  font-weight: bold;
}
```

### Reading CSS

- Read top to bottom, as you go down the Cascare what is below overwrites what's on top

### Colors

- keyword, hex, rgba, hsla
- alpha channel "a" in rgb and hsl is for transparency

```css
h1 {
  color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 1);
}
```

## Fonts

- browsers have basic fonts, for anything special you need to provide the font file in your html head
- google fonts is good to use

```html
<head>
  <link href="google font link" rel="stylesheets" />
</head>
```

```css
p {
  font-family: "Roboto", sans-serif;
  font-weight: ;
}
```

### Selectors

#### Selecting by relationship

- Direct Child: selects direct child within parent (uses > symbol)
  - parent > child
- Parent Child: selects ever child within parent (uses white space)
  - parent child
- Sibling: selects direct sibling (uses + symbol)
  - prev_sibling + next_sibling

```css
/* indirect */
section p {
  color: red;
}

/* direct */
section > p {
  color: red;
}

/* sibling */
p + p {
  color: red;
}
```

#### ID Selectors

- used for selecting distinct elements
  - #idName

```css
#zebra {
  color: red;
}
```

#### Class Selectors

- used for selecting multiple elements
  - .className

```css
.zebra {
  color: red;
}
```

#### Specificty

Higher specificity rules overwrite lower specificity rules

- type/tag - 1pt
- class - 10pt
- id - 100pt
- inline or !important - 1000pt

\*Don't use inline styling, this will make it difficult to overwrite cascading css

```css
.selector {
  color: red !important;
}
```
